This is just a note for myself because I have to put it into words.  I admit that I never watched the final videos of the Dsmp. When I stopped watching dsmp streams and its streamers the server was already pretty much inactive with the members doing various other projects. It already felt like the end of an era. At some point Tubbo and Ranboo fell apart and then Techno died and although I knew Tommy, Tubbo, Dream and the others had done their final dsmp streams I could never bring myself to watch them. Now, two years later I am here, sobbing and actually missing a time of my life that happened during Covid of all things, even though it was basically the dark ages for many people. Another reason why have not touched a single dsmp related video or vod was because I felt bad for still loving the dsmp so much. I know the members have mostly drifted apart and rarely interact (which is completely normal and happens constantly in life). I have no idea what the Dream Team is doing. But the reason I felt so bad about it is because I noticed most of the CCs donâ€™t want to be associated with the dsmp anymore, and some of them have turned out to be terrible people. But it should be fine, right? To come here and seek comfort and remember the times where Tommy and co made me laugh so hard and forget the stress of daily life. I think Skyblock at its core is the ultimate challenge in resource management. You spawn on a tiny island in an empty universe. All you have is a tree, some supplies and some dirt to stand on. You have to treasure EVERY dirt block, because if one falls into the void, there's no way to replace it and as you carefully navigate your absurd circumstance, you gain a new appreciation for the few things you have as you meticulously use them to their fullest effect. With nothing but some ice, lava and saplings you slowly transform this empty expanse into a world of your very own. Skyblock teaches us that no matter how ridiculous the odds may seem, within us resides the power to overcome these challenges and achieve something beautiful. That one day, we'll look back at where we started and be amazed by how far we've come. Technoblade

I know im extremley late to this but Heres my experiences  I remember being in yr8 in school, tommy had streamed the day before and i ddint get to watch it. I was a lonley kid in highschool, i had no friends. I was sat at a lunch table. My phone under the table (as we werent allowed to use our phones in school) watching the latest tommy stream. Some people came over to me and asked if i was watching the dream SMP..i said yes...these people were my first ever friends and we all loved the dream SMP..we would be on calls together watching the SMP..it even inspired us to start our own..but unfortunately that friendship soon ended and i was the lonley kid again and the dream SMP was my only friend. All the memories, laughs, cries, screams all came back to me. Watching this video made me realise that there was something to live for. Dream SMP carried me thru the years of my life where i wanted to end everything..and i cant thank them enough for it. Hearing technoblades passing broke my heart. I didnt leave my room for days. But i kept wachting his videos..watching the lore..everything. these guys were and still are my comfort.   Thank you so much for such amazing times..  Javier..over and out :)

Dear tommy and whoever else might read this, Here's a fun fact for you, I refused to watch this stream and video because truly deep down I didn't want it to end. Tommyinnit, Tubbo, Dream, Sapnap, Eret, George, Techno, Skippy, Bad, and everyone on this server were my high school years. I've watched them since my freshman year and the DreamSmp helped me get through tough times in my life, the story and people made me laugh, cry, and once even scream so loudly in my house I got a sore throat. This server was everything to me. It introduced me to a new favorite band (Lovejoy) and gave me a community to be in. I've met many irl friends who have this same interest with me, and I love them dearly. I got to talk to them about the new lore or streams that we thought were funny to us. Now I'm going to be a senior in high school and I'm absolutely terrified. Tommy's most recent video with his memories with Technoblade is what brought me here right now. I realize that I didn't want to watch this because he wasn't going to be in it. I am so sad that he is gone but like we all say, technoblade never dies. That saying is on my door to my room, and I see it every day. I watched this video to give my thanks on the years of joy and fun that tommy and everyone on this server gave me. I'm glad it's over so I can tell others about the most wonderful times in my life and these memories will be one of them.   Thank you tommy for all that you did for us. Thank you for giving me so much joy in the world. Thank you for introducing me to many wonderful people to watch such as yourself. Thank you for making these videos. I joined REALLY late to the Dream SMP fandom, a bit more than 1 year ago a friend was talking about an awesome community, then i got tired and asked them to tell me more. This SMP meant a lot not only for the ones part of it, but for the million people who sat until 4 am watching streams. We all became sentimentally attached to this server... to this community. We all have our favourites: our favourite animatic, our favorite DSMP song, our favourite land/place in the server, our favourite moments even our favourite lines (or maybe we have a lot of/no favorites). We have won. We have lost.  Good things must come to an end eventually. This was or is the best thing in some of our lives. I want to thank the creators who made this possible, the community, Technoblade, and all the ones that once were into all this mess. Thank you for the best moments of my life and much more's.   With all this being said...  Goodbye, Dream SMP

Dream SMP, you will be missed.
Dream SMP was basically my comfort and happiness back during covid (2020-2021 mostly) and i remember the hype and the sleepless nights i spent watching the streams and lore. Those years were the worst for my mental health and health in general.  I was deeply in depression, my grades were dropping, i had no friends other than the one friend i completely shut out at the time. I was overweight and just a horrible mess but i don't want to remember those years as only that but also the years i joined a place i could be myself in. A place where nothing is expected of me and i didn't have to meet up to expectations, i didn't have to worry about my mental health draining, i could ignore all the problems i had and as long as I felt "happy" to be anywhere but the real world, it was enough for me.  It's been awhile since i stopped watching everyone, i grew out of it, moved on and so did they. I did tear up and smile throughout the video, it just felt too nostalgic and i just didn't have it in me to pretend to be stone faced and pretend it doesn't hurt in the slightest.  I hate change and endings, they always make me greatly sad but the fact that those memories will always remain as one of the best ones really help get through the thought. I wanna thank everyone from the Dream SMP and everyone on twitch, those people were amazing and it felt like i actually had some place i could call "home".

Wow. Just... wow.  I started watching the DSMP around August of 2020. It was right when the L'Manburg war ended and the Pogtopia arc was right around the corner. I remember how I watched the Tommy and Tubbo vs Dream stream - the final battle (of sorts) - and how I screamed so loudly when moments got hype. I was invested that my brother had to come into my room like "are you okay??" from how much I was screaming from excitement.   I remember all the good times and the bad times attached to this SMP in my own personal life. When Technoblade died, my brother had died a month prior, so Techno's death hit really hard. I miss both of them so much, even though I didn't personally know one of them.   I've since then stopped really following DSMP content and have started focusing on other things, but looking back will always give me a sense of nostalgia. Tommy and the others made something special with this SMP - the stories and the characters were so engaging and no one ever truly felt like the good guy. People would argue over who was in the right and ultimately, I think that's how you know you created something complex and amazing.   And even though I hated how Tommy's story on the SMP ended, I can never forget the 2 and a half years of joy and tears and sanity this server brought me.   Thank you.

leaving a comment just for the sake of it- i got into the dsmp right in the beginning of Jan 2021 (because i already knew skeppy, bbh, and techno). i know i missed out on a lot and what i call the "prime" of the story. and i know it was dying out slowly, especially the last year or so. the dsmp gave me motivation to do the things i lost passion for (art, music). and this silly series and group of people gave me a source of joy during a weird time in my life. i daydreamt of this server and making my own self-inserted characters that were clearly extensions of my own issues. im still in that weird time in my life. it sucks that even the distractions that help ground me never stay the same.       there's a lot of things i still dont know- about the creators and the full lore because i never binge-watched the streams or became full-fledged obsessed with all the creators. i can't keep up with everyone and everything, and i dont have people in the community to keep me in check. and i still have questions; is the server shutting down?; are we still gonna see these people together in streams? i think things are prettier in the past but i can't help but feel sad that i've watched so much change over such a little span of time. everyone's growing, moving out, having relationships, careers thriving. i've changed too, and for some reason its upsetting. i know there are new things ahead of us, but i still feel like i lost something. though i lost interest in the smp (and this side of youtube), i hate that a part of me is still hopeful that maybe it really isnt over.       i can't fix any of this, but thank you. for everything. im glad that it happened, and im glad that we are doing things that make us happy, even if they aren't always the same things. o7 to this server. and even more, a teary eyed o7 to techno, who was there from before i knew of this server. <3

So good that it ended
AWHHHHHH OMG TOO MANY RANDOM MEMORIES KEEP IT FOREVER WE WILL ALWAYS REMEMBER
Man. It's insane to think that this has finally come to a close. I still remember the first time I clicked on a tommyinnit video and having my throat feel so hoarse from laughing. I remember finding Wilbur, Techno, Tubbo and everyone else through Tommy and the Dream Smp. Sometimes I wonder how I managed to get through COVID and all the lockdowns without going crazy and then I think back to how I'd join every stream I could, following and turning on as many twitch and YouTube notifications that my phone would handle, reading fan works of all the imaginative ideas of the community, listening on loop to the banger songs and just scrolling through twitter and looking at the geniunly inspiring art and animation. The Dream Smp was a new chapter for me. I changed schools, started college and moved home. Everything in my life changed, even my interests and with that came DSMP. I've been watching since near the beginning and to be honest, I never expected I'd be here. A few months ago, I fell off a little, other intests and schoolwork being my main focus. Still, I kept my eye on it. Now it's over. I don't think I'm sad about it. I'm grateful that I got to discover all these people. Not all the contents for me of course, but Tommy's vlogs and comedy, Techno's hilarious deadpan humour- everything. It helps inspire me to be the best person I can. I'm so happy I got to see this through and I can't wait to see what's next for Tommy and everyone else. Thank you Dream Smp for creating such a beautiful time in my life, in the community's life, and in the people who are actually part of the servers life. You've changed all of us for the better. ğŸ©µ

i remember a very long time ago, i used to comment on every one of my youtuber's videos. i stopped doing that for years... i dont remember the last time i actually commented on anything. (maybe thats bcuz of my bad memory tho? idk.)   i remember seeing this random dude trend on twitter. i had no idea who this kid was. i saw this specific screenshot of this guy's pov, getting aimed at by Dream and George. which was kind of weird to me because ive been watching those guys for a good maybe 9 months before i saw this? and i didnt know this kid. then i found out it was because they were on the server. the server i had no interest in watching for some reason? even tho it was with some of my favorite guys! but nope, i just didnt wanna watch it. but this kid... this kid. this kid caught my eye and i went to watch this random person i didnt even know on the server. The Dream SMP. i dont know what it was about this guy that made me so attached... maybe it was because i saw myself in him? the hyper, clingy, annoying friend. always going around causing trouble because its fucking funny.   well that dude was Tommyinnit.   i started to watch the videos he'd post of the Dream SMP. then i realized i needed more so i started watching the VODs. then i wanted to be there in real time so i started catching streams! he became the first and only person i actually watched live. at first the stuff was entertaining but then once i realized there was lore, ugh, there was no turning back for me. i mightve not been there from the very start but my love for these people and their characters, the lore and especially L'manburg, GREW. I might not have been able to see L'manburg start from nothing to something but i still felt apart of something.   i mostly watched Tommy's pov but i eventually started to watch other pov's that wouldve contributed to Tommy's storyline. i wish i couldve known everything with EVERYONES stories but i cant change that now. doesnt mean i didnt appreciate everyone else i was introduced to, tho. some of which i never heard before, familiar faces, and some that i did know existed but never paid anything attention to. ive gotten to witness great people and see them grow and succeed!  i remember the Exile Arc being the hardest part for me. but never did i stop watching. it was at that point when i realized how big of a c!Tommy kinnie i am. im so glad i got to experience that first hand. (my comfort video is still the one where Mexican Dream came to visit Logstedshire!)   then, even better, after all of that, Tommy going to Techno's house? HA, it was the best thing ever! ive gotten to finally know Techno and his character. (doesnt help that i also realized i kin c!Techno as well...) Their dynamic is hands down my favorite. its definitely my favorite point of time during this whole thing... it was just so funny and wholesome with still a little bit of angst mixed in, ya know? im so fucking grateful i was able to experience that with them both and the fans before Techno's passing. seeing his house definitely made me cry like im sure most of yall did haha.   my comfort character was/is Ghostbur. because, cmon, of course! i didnt know c!Wilbur... when i joined, thats when he blew the nation up and c!Philza killed him. i didnt have any connection to him like most of you probably had. (i didnt go back and watch videos i missed because i feel like it was like, dramatic and cool to not know some stuff. as in like i just moved into town or something lmao) so all i knew was Ghostbur. so you could imagine my anger at his death and c!Wilbur reappearing. totalllllyyy lame.   im just so grateful i got to experience this all. even tho i had no friends that watched it... i had THEM. i wasnt alone. thank you so much, Tommy... for showing me the way. without you, i dont know when or if i wouldve ever gotten into the Dream SMP! im sorry to Dream, George and Sapnap that i ignored your server and only joined for the hyper kid LOL. but honestly, i wouldnt change a thing. it was all... perfect. it made me laugh, it made me cry, it made me angry and theorize and going crazy!!!! but i love that shit.   honestly without this, who knows how long it wouldve took me to find out my identity? i cosplayed for a while there and one time in a Wilbur cosplay and i saw myself and i knew then that i was actually a boy.   my life would be very different without you, your friends and this server, Tommy. just like how you say sometimes in your videos that we might find you annoying?   well, i never found you annoying.

You are not here to receive a gift, nor have you been called here by the individual you assume. Although you have indeed been called. You have all been called here. Into a labyrinth of sounds and smells, misdirection and misfortune. A labyrinth with no exit, a maze with no prize. You don't even realize that you are trapped. Your lust for blood has driven you in endless circles, chasing the cries of children in some unseen chamber, always seeming so near, yet somehow out of reach. But you will never find them, none of you will. This is where your story ends. And to you, my brave volunteer, who somehow found this job listing not intended for you. Although there was a way out planned for you, I have a feeling that's not what you want. I have a feeling that you are right where you want to be. I am remaining as well, I am nearby. This place will not be remembered, and the memory of everything that started this can finally begin to fade away. As the agony of every tragedy should. And to you monsters trapped in the corridors: Be still and give up your spirits, they don't belong to you. For most of you, I believe there is peace and perhaps more waiting for you after the smoke clears. Although, for one of you, the darkest pit of Hell has opened to swallow you whole, so don't keep the devil waiting, old friend. My daughter, if you can hear me, I knew you would return as well. It's in your nature to protect the innocent. This ends for all of us. End communication.

Those who watched since the beginning: It's an unfortunate truth that the things that bring us the most happiness, the moments that feel like they'll last forever, are often the ones that are most fleeting. We can become so consumed by joy that we forget to prepare ourselves for the inevitable end.  But when that end does come, it can be devastating. It feels like a piece of ourselves has been taken away, like we've lost a part of our identity. We mourn the loss of what once was, and we grieve for what we know can never be again.  The pain is real, and it cuts deep. It can be hard to see past the darkness and remember that life is full of new experiences and new joys waiting to be discovered. We may feel lost, adrift in a sea of uncertainty and sorrow.  But it's important to remember that even in our darkest moments, we are never truly alone. There are people around us who care, who want to see us happy again. And even though it may feel like the end of the world, there is always hope for a new beginning.  So as we mourn the loss of what once was, let us also look forward to what can be.
